:"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Waléran","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Walburn  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Walburn","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>burg</i> ‘stronghold’.  St Walburg  (  d. ?779 ) was of Anglo-Saxon origin, and the original form of her name was <i>Wealdburh</i> or <i>Wealburh</i>. She became abbess of Heidenheim and her relics are preserved at Eichstatt."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Waléran de Breteuil II,  Seig de Breteuil e de Creil was born in 1065, in Breteuil-sur-Iton, Eure, Upper Normandy, France, his father, Waleran de Breteuil I, was 35 and his mother, Adelise de Clermont, was 46. He married Judith Ivette De Saint-Just En Chaussée in 1091. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died in 1124, in his hometown, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1065–1124":"1065–1124","1059–1112":"1059–1112","1066–Male":"1066–Surnud","1074–1128":"1074–1128","1091–1146":"1091–1146","1095–1147":"1095–1147","1096–1115":"1096–1115","1030–1084":"1030–1084","1020–1089":"1020–1089","1091":"1091","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","1020":"1020","1030":"1030","1096":"1096","1074":"1074","1095":"1095","1084":"1084","ABT 1096":"umbes 1096","Abt 1064":"umbes 1064","1128":"1128","25 de fevereiro de 1084":"25